1
00:00:05,440 --> 00:00:08,009
When Oh Jak Doo didn't say
anything...

2
00:00:08,009 --> 00:00:10,250
and ran away to the countryside,

3
00:00:10,650 --> 00:00:12,019
that's when you were supposed to
watch a movie with me.

4
00:00:12,580 --> 00:00:14,789
You are not going to make me
wait again, are you?

5
00:00:14,789 --> 00:00:15,949
No, no, no!

6
00:00:16,589 --> 00:00:17,620
Never!

7
00:00:20,530 --> 00:00:23,660
I met Gyeong Sook and her husband
at the broadcasting station.

8
00:00:23,660 --> 00:00:25,260
Jae Hyung said we should
buy them dinner...

9
00:00:25,300 --> 00:00:27,030
since the documentary
went well.

10
00:00:27,030 --> 00:00:28,199
What should we do?

11
00:00:28,829 --> 00:00:31,100
We can watch the movie tomorrow.

12
00:00:31,640 --> 00:00:33,299
Do you want me to go there?

13
00:00:33,299 --> 00:00:35,170
(Do you want me to go there?)

14
00:00:41,609 --> 00:00:42,649
No, it's okay.

15
00:00:46,689 --> 00:00:49,920
(Episode 23: Marriage is
having someone you always care.)

16
00:00:57,200 --> 00:00:58,600
I thought you are going to be
here at night.

17
00:00:59,700 --> 00:01:01,770
My student doesn't have
sensitive hands.

18
00:01:01,770 --> 00:01:03,329
So I was worried.

19
00:01:03,329 --> 00:01:06,170
Aren't you here because you are
not meeting Seung Joo anymore?

20
00:01:11,640 --> 00:01:14,480
Why are you looking at me like that?

21
00:01:14,480 --> 00:01:16,010
Because I don't even know
where to start.

22
00:01:17,980 --> 00:01:19,049
Right...

23
00:01:20,019 --> 00:01:22,150
I dropped by the broadcasting
station this morning,

24
00:01:22,150 --> 00:01:24,989
and I knew you wouldn't be able to
see the movie with her tonight.

25
00:01:25,459 --> 00:01:27,390
I knew she was going to ditch you.

26
00:01:28,689 --> 00:01:30,700
Did you meet Seung Joo?

27
00:01:30,700 --> 00:01:34,299
No, I just heard something
at the broadcasting station.

28
00:01:34,900 --> 00:01:35,930
What is it?

29
00:01:35,930 --> 00:01:37,500
Well, the documentary
was successful.

30
00:01:37,500 --> 00:01:39,700
Of course, it's positive news.

31
00:01:40,340 --> 00:01:42,810
It's just a problem that
you don't know what I know.

32
00:01:42,810 --> 00:01:45,010
Don't talk around and
be complicated.

33
00:01:45,010 --> 00:01:47,849
Can you not go back
to the countryside?

34
00:01:49,510 --> 00:01:52,519
Can you just live in Seoul?

35
00:01:52,519 --> 00:01:55,819
Han Seung Joo is the only one
who can suggest that to me.

36
00:01:55,819 --> 00:01:56,890
You can't do that.

37
00:01:56,890 --> 00:01:59,859
It looks like she can't say it
even though she wants to.

38
00:01:59,859 --> 00:02:02,530
- That's why I'm saying this to you.
- She and I can...

39
00:02:02,989 --> 00:02:04,900
talk about everything.

40
00:02:04,900 --> 00:02:08,530
Then how did you not know that she
got the job offer from the station?

41
00:02:09,569 --> 00:02:13,569
You know how much Seung Joo wants
to work at the broadcasting station.

42
00:02:14,539 --> 00:02:17,539
- Of course, I know.
- She can do it now.

43
00:02:17,539 --> 00:02:19,780
But she's supposed to go to
the countryside with you.

44
00:02:20,210 --> 00:02:22,180
I'm sure that's why she couldn't
talk about it freely.

45
00:02:22,479 --> 00:02:25,080
That's why I'm telling you
about it in advance.

46
00:02:25,080 --> 00:02:26,620
Are you Seung Joo?

47
00:02:27,389 --> 00:02:30,120
If there's any good news,
she'll tell me first.

48
00:02:30,120 --> 00:02:33,159
If she's concerned about anything,
she'll also tell me first.

49
00:02:33,460 --> 00:02:35,830
Who do you think you are
to have these unnecessary worries?

50
00:02:36,490 --> 00:02:37,530
I was just...

51
00:02:37,530 --> 00:02:39,659
You know you have to focus
as much as you can...

52
00:02:39,659 --> 00:02:41,430
and that's not even enough
to be better than now.

53
00:02:41,430 --> 00:02:43,639
Do you think you can make one
proper gayageum before you die...

54
00:02:43,639 --> 00:02:45,800
when you are this distracted
by everything?

55
00:02:48,439 --> 00:02:50,310
Hold the wood
and think about yourself.

56
00:02:53,680 --> 00:02:55,680
Let me pick up the phone first.

57
00:02:58,319 --> 00:02:59,349
Hello?

58
00:02:59,650 --> 00:03:02,219
Oh, Mrs. Park!

59
00:03:02,550 --> 00:03:05,620
Did you finish the paperwork?

60
00:03:05,620 --> 00:03:06,729
Excuse me.

61
00:03:07,159 --> 00:03:08,229
I see.

62
00:03:08,689 --> 00:03:11,430
Really? If you look at the file...

63
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:18,900
I'll see you at the office.

64
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:20,909
- Take care.
- Take care, sir.

65
00:03:20,909 --> 00:03:22,210
Take care, sir!

66
00:03:23,270 --> 00:03:24,340
Jae Hyung, I have to go.

67
00:03:24,340 --> 00:03:26,509
We are going to go get some coffee.
Why don't you join us?

68
00:03:26,509 --> 00:03:28,449
I'll do that next time.
Bye! I'm going!

69
00:03:28,449 --> 00:03:29,509
But...

70
00:03:31,449 --> 00:03:33,789
She can take the job
for our new project.

71
00:03:33,789 --> 00:03:35,889
We don't know if she's going to
work with us or not yet.

72
00:03:36,020 --> 00:03:38,819
Who can say no to the position
at the broadcasting station?

73
00:03:38,819 --> 00:03:41,789
That's where she always came to
get confirmations for her work.

74
00:03:42,159 --> 00:03:45,900
We can just make a new team
for the new project for her.

75
00:03:45,900 --> 00:03:47,900
Should we?

76
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:49,500
Sir!

77
00:03:50,169 --> 00:03:51,539
Yes, Han Seung Joo?

78
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:53,069
Excuse me.

79
00:03:57,879 --> 00:03:59,810
I couldn't tell
you about it properly...

80
00:03:59,810 --> 00:04:01,750
when we were in the restaurant
because there were other people.

81
00:04:02,949 --> 00:04:04,750
I thought about it a lot.

82
00:04:05,150 --> 00:04:07,889
But I came here because I thought
it would be better...

83
00:04:07,919 --> 00:04:09,949
if I told you what my opinion is.

84
00:04:10,020 --> 00:04:11,360
Tell me what it is.

85
00:04:11,620 --> 00:04:14,229
First, I would like to thank
you for proposing...

86
00:04:14,229 --> 00:04:16,860
such a wonderful opportunity for me.

87
00:04:18,100 --> 00:04:21,730
I heard you applied
for a job at our station before.

88
00:04:22,529 --> 00:04:23,899
But my situation changed...

89
00:04:24,339 --> 00:04:27,110
a little bit since then.

90
00:04:27,569 --> 00:04:28,639
So...

91
00:04:29,410 --> 00:04:31,579
You might think that I'm rude,

92
00:04:32,439 --> 00:04:35,410
but could I work
by contract for each program?

93
00:04:36,149 --> 00:04:39,550
There are some producers
who work by contract like that.

94
00:04:39,550 --> 00:04:41,220
If you could consider my situation,

95
00:04:41,250 --> 00:04:43,459
I can work harder than anyone else.

96
00:04:44,860 --> 00:04:48,029
The reason why I'm trying
to recruit and hire you is...

97
00:04:48,029 --> 00:04:51,160
because
our organization needs you.

98
00:04:53,329 --> 00:04:54,600
I see.

99
00:04:54,699 --> 00:04:56,500
I don't know what happened
to make you turn down...

100
00:04:56,500 --> 00:04:59,069
such a great opportunity,
so take care of that.

101
00:05:00,639 --> 00:05:02,509
I'll wait to hear good news.

102
00:05:02,540 --> 00:05:04,139
Think about it and contact us.

103
00:05:04,810 --> 00:05:06,509
- Okay.
- Goodbye.

104
00:05:41,279 --> 00:05:42,410
Where are you?

105
00:05:46,889 --> 00:05:47,920
Home.

106
00:05:51,660 --> 00:05:53,389
("Home")

107
00:06:00,300 --> 00:06:01,399
("I'm sorry that...")

108
00:06:03,100 --> 00:06:04,370
I'm sorry that I couldn't keep...

109
00:06:04,800 --> 00:06:06,870
my promise to watch a movie.

110
00:06:08,769 --> 00:06:11,779
It's okay.
I didn't keep my promise back then.

111
00:06:19,480 --> 00:06:21,750
I think I'm going to be
a little late today.

112
00:06:25,920 --> 00:06:27,029
I'll wait.

113
00:06:33,259 --> 00:06:34,399
Okay.

114
00:07:02,029 --> 00:07:03,399
What is the world like?

115
00:07:04,300 --> 00:07:05,899
The world?

116
00:07:07,269 --> 00:07:08,430
It's frustrating.

117
00:07:09,829 --> 00:07:11,100
The world...

118
00:07:12,540 --> 00:07:15,639
labels me...

119
00:07:17,540 --> 00:07:19,810
the minute I leave home.

120
00:07:22,449 --> 00:07:23,550
Woman,

121
00:07:24,579 --> 00:07:25,649
born from poor parents,

122
00:07:26,920 --> 00:07:28,889
and graduated
from a third-rate university.

123
00:07:31,620 --> 00:07:33,759
Do you know how hard...

124
00:07:34,930 --> 00:07:37,129
it is to remove
even one of those labels?

125
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:44,040
You have to be
cowardly at least 1,000 times,

126
00:07:45,639 --> 00:07:49,209
and get rid
of your pride 10,000 times.

127
00:07:50,540 --> 00:07:52,740
Still then, you're not even sure
whether that will be enough or not.

128
00:07:56,079 --> 00:07:58,120
But...

129
00:07:59,149 --> 00:08:02,620
if I do a good job on this project,

130
00:08:03,490 --> 00:08:05,860
I'm going to hide...

131
00:08:06,389 --> 00:08:09,759
all of those labels
behind my name, Han Seung Joo.

132
00:08:14,629 --> 00:08:16,170
Then it ended up to be...

133
00:08:16,170 --> 00:08:18,000
better that Seung Joo
didn't get that job that time.

134
00:08:18,069 --> 00:08:19,199
Of course.

135
00:08:19,199 --> 00:08:21,939
Recruit and hire,
doesn't it even sound special?

136
00:08:22,370 --> 00:08:24,379
Remember that producer Jeong gave
us the worst time...

137
00:08:24,379 --> 00:08:25,839
when we went to the broadcasting
station to get confirmation.

138
00:08:25,839 --> 00:08:28,509
Show him how good you are
and defeat him.

139
00:08:28,550 --> 00:08:30,850
Do you think I'm going to the
broadcasting station for a revenge?

140
00:08:30,850 --> 00:08:32,950
When you applied for that job last
time, producer Jeong criticized...

141
00:08:32,950 --> 00:08:35,549
you the most for not having
a documentary on your filmography.

142
00:08:35,820 --> 00:08:37,419
You took care of that.

143
00:08:37,419 --> 00:08:39,659
The world is in your hands.

144
00:08:39,659 --> 00:08:42,159
Of course. What should we eat?

145
00:08:42,159 --> 00:08:44,600
This isn't a normal celebration.

146
00:08:45,259 --> 00:08:48,929
I decided
to go to the country with him.

147
00:08:49,129 --> 00:08:50,200
What?

148
00:08:50,570 --> 00:08:51,769
After the documentary,

149
00:08:51,940 --> 00:08:53,740
we're going to live
in the country together.

150
00:08:53,909 --> 00:08:56,909
What will you do in the country?

151
00:08:56,909 --> 00:08:58,580
I can come to Seoul sometimes...

152
00:08:58,580 --> 00:09:00,009
if someone requests a job.

153
00:09:00,009 --> 00:09:02,580
So does that mean that
you rejected that offer?

154
00:09:03,779 --> 00:09:04,919
I didn't yet.

155
00:09:06,120 --> 00:09:07,720
To be honest, I became greedy.

156
00:09:07,750 --> 00:09:09,250
That's not greed.

157
00:09:09,289 --> 00:09:11,690
If people knew how hard
you worked to remain in this field,

158
00:09:11,690 --> 00:09:13,860
they wouldn't ask
you to keep your promise.

159
00:09:14,460 --> 00:09:16,799
I have to be separated from him.

160
00:09:16,830 --> 00:09:19,659
Tell him to live in Seoul together.

161
00:09:19,730 --> 00:09:22,700
After watching the documentary,
even I wouldn't be able to say that.

162
00:09:22,730 --> 00:09:25,070
When I got the offer,

163
00:09:25,299 --> 00:09:26,940
it was my dream,

164
00:09:27,110 --> 00:09:29,340
but I wanted to do it more
because of realistic reasons.

165
00:09:29,340 --> 00:09:30,779
What kind of realistic reasons?

166
00:09:30,940 --> 00:09:33,379
If you have 2 or 3 years
of work experience...

167
00:09:33,379 --> 00:09:35,049
at a broadcasting station,
it is more stable...

168
00:09:35,049 --> 00:09:36,879
to work as a freelancer
in the country.

169
00:09:36,980 --> 00:09:39,250
It would also be
easier to get shows.

170
00:09:39,250 --> 00:09:41,490
Seeing that she's thinking
like that,

171
00:09:41,519 --> 00:09:42,990
she must have really decided to bury
her bones in the country.

172
00:09:42,990 --> 00:09:44,690
Oh, my. What should we do?

173
00:09:45,620 --> 00:09:47,690
Doesn't Hyuk know yet?

174
00:09:47,860 --> 00:09:48,960
No.

175
00:09:49,960 --> 00:09:52,100
I'm not confident of being
separated from him.

176
00:09:52,159 --> 00:09:55,070
It's my greed...

177
00:09:55,070 --> 00:09:56,840
to ask him to live in Seoul.

178
00:09:57,840 --> 00:09:59,269
I can't see his face yet...

179
00:09:59,269 --> 00:10:01,340
because I haven't organized
my thoughts yet.

180
00:10:01,440 --> 00:10:02,840
How can I tell him?

181
00:10:03,070 --> 00:10:06,539
You should decide with your head,
not your heart.

182
00:10:06,539 --> 00:10:08,509
You won't be able to stand
giving up all of your work...

183
00:10:08,509 --> 00:10:10,519
and live in the country
only because of Hyuk.

184
00:10:10,519 --> 00:10:12,350
She's not giving up.

185
00:10:12,379 --> 00:10:13,889
I wish Seung Joo would be
with him more...

186
00:10:13,889 --> 00:10:15,549
and work less.

187
00:10:15,620 --> 00:10:17,620
You can't survive only with dreams.
Aren't you going to make money?

188
00:10:17,720 --> 00:10:20,490
Don't you remember how happy
Seung Joo is when she's with him?

189
00:10:20,490 --> 00:10:23,029
I know, but she's not in
a situation...

190
00:10:23,029 --> 00:10:25,230
where she can just be with him.

191
00:10:25,259 --> 00:10:26,529
Still...

192
00:10:37,009 --> 00:10:38,240
This is the news.

193
00:10:41,080 --> 00:10:44,549
This is the subject
of the piano recital.

194
00:10:48,919 --> 00:10:49,990
Are you home?

195
00:10:51,320 --> 00:10:52,419
Yes.

196
00:10:54,029 --> 00:10:55,590
- No.
- That's not enough.

197
00:10:55,990 --> 00:10:57,230
There's not enough food.

198
00:10:57,230 --> 00:10:59,700
- Is it okay?
- No.

199
00:11:02,129 --> 00:11:03,539
Should we eat?

200
00:11:04,169 --> 00:11:05,840
This is really nice.

201
00:11:06,370 --> 00:11:07,470
It's really delicious.

202
00:11:08,470 --> 00:11:10,809
The sudden rescue request of a hero.

203
00:11:13,649 --> 00:11:16,350
Yes, I'm being in the headlines.

204
00:11:18,879 --> 00:11:21,490
You can see a square filled...

205
00:11:21,490 --> 00:11:23,389
with impressive buildings.

206
00:11:32,059 --> 00:11:33,129
How about...

207
00:11:36,700 --> 00:11:37,940
getting married?

208
00:11:46,110 --> 00:11:47,149
Why?

209
00:11:50,250 --> 00:11:51,980
Are you not going to get married?

210
00:11:55,250 --> 00:11:56,759
Not like last time.

211
00:11:59,090 --> 00:12:01,830
When you first came to me...

212
00:12:03,029 --> 00:12:04,360
and asked me to marry you,

213
00:12:05,429 --> 00:12:06,769
and asked me to be your husband,

214
00:12:09,200 --> 00:12:10,470
it sounded like you were asking...

215
00:12:11,269 --> 00:12:12,970
me to save you to me.

216
00:12:16,309 --> 00:12:17,340
But...

217
00:12:18,980 --> 00:12:19,980
but it also sounds like last time...

218
00:12:21,549 --> 00:12:22,980
today.

219
00:12:27,720 --> 00:12:29,220
Why didn't you tell me...

220
00:12:31,120 --> 00:12:32,289
about the broadcasting station?

221
00:12:35,230 --> 00:12:36,759
I already know everything.

222
00:12:39,429 --> 00:12:40,769
Why aren't you telling me?

223
00:12:43,500 --> 00:12:44,600
I was just...

224
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:47,210
sorry.

225
00:12:47,769 --> 00:12:48,809
Why are you sorry?

226
00:12:50,779 --> 00:12:52,580
I thought I might not be
able to keep...

227
00:12:53,909 --> 00:12:55,879
my promise to go with you.

228
00:12:58,279 --> 00:13:00,590
Are you going to marry me...

229
00:13:02,820 --> 00:13:04,059
to make me go back
feeling relieved?

230
00:13:05,919 --> 00:13:08,289
I want to be with you...

231
00:13:11,799 --> 00:13:13,570
rather than a marriage like that.

232
00:13:17,269 --> 00:13:18,600
I'll be...

233
00:13:21,370 --> 00:13:22,509
by your side.

234
00:13:24,779 --> 00:13:27,379
I know how hard it is...

235
00:13:27,950 --> 00:13:30,519
for you to be in Seoul.

236
00:13:30,519 --> 00:13:32,419
That's my issue to take care of.

237
00:13:54,210 --> 00:13:56,509
Gushing.

238
00:13:59,240 --> 00:14:00,480
Do you remember?

239
00:14:05,679 --> 00:14:06,789
Yes.

240
00:14:09,850 --> 00:14:11,919
Why are you throwing it out?

241
00:14:17,299 --> 00:14:19,230
Isn't it a good thing...

242
00:14:19,799 --> 00:14:22,700
that you got to quit
that broadcasting system?

243
00:14:25,440 --> 00:14:26,970
That's why I saved them.

244
00:14:29,169 --> 00:14:30,340
Let's go outside.

245
00:14:42,590 --> 00:14:43,690
Cheers.

246
00:14:44,889 --> 00:14:46,519
I mean... It's...

247
00:14:46,960 --> 00:14:49,629
Don't we have to cheers...

248
00:14:52,799 --> 00:14:54,429
in a couple's manner?

249
00:15:06,139 --> 00:15:07,809
I love you.

250
00:15:13,789 --> 00:15:17,220
I have to say this...

251
00:15:18,789 --> 00:15:20,830
when I really want to get married
to someone.

252
00:15:23,529 --> 00:15:24,759
You're right.

253
00:15:40,409 --> 00:15:43,250
So you're saying you're not going
back to the country?

254
00:15:43,549 --> 00:15:46,250
I just switched my time there
to the one in Seoul.

255
00:15:46,919 --> 00:15:49,419
It's not that I should
come back to Seoul when I need to.

256
00:15:49,620 --> 00:15:51,759
I'll be going to the country
when I'm needed.

257
00:15:51,960 --> 00:15:53,529
Is it because of Seung Joo?

258
00:15:54,090 --> 00:15:55,659
No, it's because of me.

259
00:15:55,789 --> 00:15:58,860
For what I understand, you are
the opposite of city life.

260
00:16:00,200 --> 00:16:03,399
Instead of just missing Seung Joo
in the country,

261
00:16:03,570 --> 00:16:05,470
I rather see her here...

262
00:16:05,539 --> 00:16:07,710
and endure my life in Seoul.

