00:32:04,099 --> 00:32:05,759
Are you talking badly of me?

522
00:32:05,759 --> 00:32:08,000
I felt bad when I was young,

523
00:32:08,700 --> 00:32:11,670
but now that I think of it,
if you only sacrificed for me,

524
00:32:11,670 --> 00:32:13,769
I wouldn't have felt so easy
like how I'm feeling right now.

525
00:32:13,769 --> 00:32:17,539
Are you being sarcastic about how
I shouldn't expect so much from you?

526
00:32:17,539 --> 00:32:20,079
Before, I used to take care of
your living expenses...

527
00:32:20,079 --> 00:32:23,519
and Seung Tae's school fee...

528
00:32:23,519 --> 00:32:26,450
that I never found joy in working,

529
00:32:27,150 --> 00:32:30,059
but now it's different even though
I'm working the same job.

530
00:32:30,059 --> 00:32:32,589
I don't expect much from you either.

531
00:32:32,589 --> 00:32:35,559
So please just get married...

532
00:32:35,559 --> 00:32:37,700
before Jak Doo sees
the real side of you.

533
00:32:41,130 --> 00:32:43,029
Don't judge me.

534
00:32:43,440 --> 00:32:45,839
I'm just being honest.

535
00:32:45,839 --> 00:32:48,470
What? Is it a crime to want
a rich son-in-law?

536
00:32:48,470 --> 00:32:50,480
Is that such a crime?

537
00:32:50,740 --> 00:32:52,740
He has an unrivaled skill.

538
00:32:52,740 --> 00:32:55,009
- He can just...
- He's...

539
00:32:55,210 --> 00:32:57,619
someone who should not
care about money.

540
00:32:58,180 --> 00:33:00,549
Even if we get married,
I'll be the one earning.

541
00:33:02,049 --> 00:33:03,819
- What did you say?
- So...

542
00:33:03,819 --> 00:33:05,660
please don't tell me
to get married,

543
00:33:05,660 --> 00:33:07,960
thinking he'll bring us a fortune.

544
00:33:08,589 --> 00:33:11,559
I won't sacrifice myself for you,

545
00:33:11,559 --> 00:33:13,769
but I will do my duty as a daughter.

546
00:33:14,299 --> 00:33:18,140
Then why don't you give me
a monthly payment as a daughter?

547
00:33:21,809 --> 00:33:24,640
Well, I'm getting good responses.

548
00:33:24,640 --> 00:33:26,240
Our foundation...

549
00:33:26,240 --> 00:33:29,009
Hey, wait. Excuse me, Seung Joo.

550
00:33:29,009 --> 00:33:30,349
Hold on. I'll call you back.

551
00:33:31,549 --> 00:33:34,450
Hey, what are you doing here?

552
00:33:35,450 --> 00:33:38,690
- Isn't he at his workshop?
- Wait.

553
00:33:39,019 --> 00:33:40,160
He is,

554
00:33:41,259 --> 00:33:46,200
but while he was trying to teach me,
one of his musicians...

555
00:33:46,200 --> 00:33:50,000
who was practicing visited him
as the string broke.

556
00:33:50,000 --> 00:33:52,740
Oh, he must be fixing it now.

557
00:33:52,799 --> 00:33:53,809
That's right.

558
00:33:54,140 --> 00:33:55,569
So...

559
00:33:55,940 --> 00:33:59,710
I think you can wait for him
with me here.

560
00:34:00,680 --> 00:34:02,880
Can I not watch him
fixing the string?

561
00:34:03,309 --> 00:34:05,119
That's not what it is.

562
00:34:06,079 --> 00:34:07,420
The gayageum player is...

563
00:34:09,489 --> 00:34:10,619
Jang Eun Jo.

564
00:34:11,389 --> 00:34:12,489
What?

565
00:34:12,860 --> 00:34:14,159
It's Jang Eun Jo.

566
00:34:14,530 --> 00:34:16,230
Jang?

567
00:34:16,829 --> 00:34:18,260
It's Jang Eun Jo.

568
00:34:22,630 --> 00:34:24,039
I'll go watch then.

569
00:34:24,070 --> 00:34:25,099
What?

570
00:34:25,440 --> 00:34:27,869
Seung Joo...

571
00:34:33,849 --> 00:34:36,210
Silk strings are
really weak at humidity.

572
00:34:36,210 --> 00:34:38,150
The hot weather loosens it a lot.

573
00:34:53,869 --> 00:34:55,070
It's been a while.

574
00:34:55,530 --> 00:34:56,570
Hi.

575
00:34:57,400 --> 00:34:58,739
Is it going to take a while?

576
00:34:59,469 --> 00:35:00,670
No, it's almost done.

577
00:35:02,369 --> 00:35:03,980
If you try to tighten
the strings up too much...

578
00:35:04,380 --> 00:35:05,440
to make sounds...

579
00:35:05,639 --> 00:35:07,780
when they are loose,
they can break.

580
00:35:08,110 --> 00:35:09,150
I know.

581
00:35:18,659 --> 00:35:20,030
You have to have spare strings.

582
00:35:20,059 --> 00:35:21,190
I see.

583
00:35:25,400 --> 00:35:28,070
The body of your gayageum can be
a bit shaky during the performance.

584
00:35:28,070 --> 00:35:29,869
So don't forget the rosin powder.

585
00:35:31,340 --> 00:35:32,369
Thank you.

586
00:36:07,139 --> 00:36:08,469
Eun Jo, if you are done,

587
00:36:08,539 --> 00:36:10,539
I need to have a word with you.

588
00:36:11,539 --> 00:36:12,639
Okay.

589
00:36:16,719 --> 00:36:18,980
- I'll go.
- Good luck with your performance.

590
00:36:24,760 --> 00:36:25,789
Hey,

591
00:36:38,469 --> 00:36:40,610
Strings of Gayageum...

592
00:36:40,639 --> 00:36:41,940
easily break during performances.

593
00:36:42,210 --> 00:36:45,210
For some performances, gayageum
makers even stay at the backstage.

594
00:36:45,710 --> 00:36:47,050
That's not what it is.

595
00:36:49,550 --> 00:36:51,349
I feel a bit weird.

596
00:36:52,849 --> 00:36:54,789
It's not because of Jang Eun Jo.

597
00:36:55,849 --> 00:36:58,489
It's because of myself.

598
00:37:01,190 --> 00:37:02,360
What is it?

599
00:37:02,360 --> 00:37:03,460
It feels like...

600
00:37:04,099 --> 00:37:05,429
I have...

601
00:37:05,829 --> 00:37:07,800
forgotten about something.

602
00:37:10,539 --> 00:37:12,400
Working at the broadcasting station,

603
00:37:13,409 --> 00:37:15,170
I had a lot of things
I needed to take care of.

604
00:37:16,139 --> 00:37:17,940
But working there was fun.

605
00:37:19,539 --> 00:37:22,179
So I couldn't really think about
other than my work.

606
00:37:24,179 --> 00:37:26,280
But how can I be like this?

607
00:37:29,690 --> 00:37:31,119
Did something happen to you?

608
00:37:35,559 --> 00:37:38,000
I've forgotten about...

609
00:37:39,599 --> 00:37:41,599
who Oh Jak Doo really was.

610
00:37:45,340 --> 00:37:48,309
They are the same gayageums
you've been making.

611
00:37:50,610 --> 00:37:52,480
When we were filming
the documentary,

612
00:37:53,510 --> 00:37:56,010
how you looked at the studio
in the countryside...

613
00:37:57,150 --> 00:37:58,650
was very different from how you are
here. Did you know that?

614
00:38:00,889 --> 00:38:01,889
No, I didn't know that.

615
00:38:04,820 --> 00:38:07,030
You are at somewhere
you don't belong.

616
00:38:08,429 --> 00:38:09,659
How can you not know?

617
00:38:10,199 --> 00:38:11,300
I...

618
00:38:12,730 --> 00:38:15,429
I chose to be here because
I want to be next to you, Seung Joo.

619
00:38:16,170 --> 00:38:17,469
Is that right though?

620
00:38:20,039 --> 00:38:22,010
Someone I like...

621
00:38:23,269 --> 00:38:25,010
doesn't look happy at all...

622
00:38:27,409 --> 00:38:29,750
when he's doing his job.

623
00:38:31,550 --> 00:38:33,920
So I don't know if I should make you
stay here to be next to me.

624
00:38:39,719 --> 00:38:41,960
I have to reconsider it.

625
00:38:43,460 --> 00:38:44,559
About what?

626
00:38:46,230 --> 00:38:47,369
Us.

627
00:38:57,110 --> 00:38:58,909
You made the right decision.

628
00:38:59,340 --> 00:39:00,380
You have to go if you have to go.

629
00:39:00,809 --> 00:39:03,250
You've been holding on to
somewhere you don't like.

630
00:39:03,309 --> 00:39:04,820
Just watching you is painful.

631
00:39:07,050 --> 00:39:09,789
I'm going to be here
once every two weeks.

632
00:39:09,820 --> 00:39:11,719
So don't forget your homework.

633
00:39:11,719 --> 00:39:14,329
I told you I'll do it!

634
00:39:14,889 --> 00:39:17,400
Do you not need anything
to bring there by the way?

635
00:39:18,159 --> 00:39:20,670
What should I give you?

636
00:39:23,329 --> 00:39:25,199
Do you want to take this with you?

637
00:39:32,340 --> 00:39:33,449
Take this.

638
00:39:33,510 --> 00:39:35,880
I live on the ground.
Why would I need that?

639
00:39:35,880 --> 00:39:37,179
Do you live in a mud hut?

640
00:39:37,219 --> 00:39:38,380
But...

641
00:39:38,550 --> 00:39:41,090
it's the most comfortable
place for me to live.

642
00:39:41,090 --> 00:39:43,219
You can take my car if you want.

643
00:39:43,289 --> 00:39:45,719
I stay in the mountain
6 days a week.

644
00:39:46,090 --> 00:39:47,130
So I don't need a car.

645
00:39:47,130 --> 00:39:49,760
If I tell you to take it,
just take it!

646
00:39:50,199 --> 00:39:52,230
Why are you yelling at me?

647
00:39:52,260 --> 00:39:54,170
I express my affection
by spending money...

648
00:39:55,730 --> 00:39:57,039
Money is the only thing I have.

649
00:39:57,570 --> 00:39:59,440
Since I was young,

650
00:39:59,699 --> 00:40:01,409
that's how I've been living my life.

651
00:40:01,610 --> 00:40:03,940
So I can only feel comfortable
after giving you something.

652
00:40:03,940 --> 00:40:06,179
You don't want the vacuum cleaner,
but you don't want the car either.

653
00:40:06,539 --> 00:40:07,550
Well...

654
00:40:08,280 --> 00:40:09,710
Should I just give you cash?

655
00:40:09,849 --> 00:40:11,880
We are friends. We should know
how we feel even without a word.

656
00:40:13,320 --> 00:40:14,989
I can feel your heart,

657
00:40:15,519 --> 00:40:16,989
Eric Cho Bong Sik.

658
00:40:17,960 --> 00:40:19,059
Is this enough?

659
00:40:19,559 --> 00:40:20,760
Well...

660
00:40:21,460 --> 00:40:23,860
You are the cool one
in this relationship.

661
00:40:51,090 --> 00:40:53,429
This is when Oh Jak Doo
comes to Seoul.

662
00:40:54,630 --> 00:40:56,329
And...

663
00:41:05,369 --> 00:41:06,440
This is...

664
00:41:07,170 --> 00:41:08,440
when Han Seung Joo
comes here.

665
00:41:14,079 --> 00:41:16,079
From now on, we are going to be...

666
00:41:16,210 --> 00:41:17,519
in a long-distance relationship.

667
00:41:25,059 --> 00:41:27,230
Have you heard of it before?

668
00:41:27,289 --> 00:41:29,030
Long-distance?

669
00:41:29,429 --> 00:41:30,500
No.

670
00:41:32,199 --> 00:41:34,630
It's a romantic relationship where
they are physically far away...

671
00:41:34,630 --> 00:41:37,070
because of working overseas and
countryside, or studying overseas.

672
00:41:38,139 --> 00:41:40,940
So even though we are far away,
nothing changes.

673
00:41:42,340 --> 00:41:44,679
We live our own lives
at our own places.

674
00:41:44,679 --> 00:41:45,780
Then?

675
00:41:45,780 --> 00:41:48,010
We meet each other
just once a week.

676
00:41:48,050 --> 00:41:49,280
And we don't see each other
forever again.

677
00:41:50,949 --> 00:41:53,889
But we've become husband and wife
as soon as we met each other.

678
00:41:53,920 --> 00:41:55,150
So what are we now?

679
00:41:55,949 --> 00:41:56,960
We are dating.

680
00:42:00,989 --> 00:42:04,260
When you arrive at your place,
the first thing you have to do is...

681
00:42:04,260 --> 00:42:06,059
finding the best spot
for your phone to work.

682
00:42:06,769 --> 00:42:09,369
8am and 9pm.

683
00:42:09,829 --> 00:42:11,769
We are going to talk on the phone
twice a day.

684
00:42:11,769 --> 00:42:13,340
That's the basis of
the long-distance relationship.

685
00:42:20,349 --> 00:42:21,510
Hello?

686
00:42:22,710 --> 00:42:23,780
Hi.

687
00:42:24,780 --> 00:42:26,079
Hi.

688
00:42:27,550 --> 00:42:29,090
This is a bit awkward, isn't it?

689
00:42:29,190 --> 00:42:31,489
Are you going to work now?

690
00:42:31,760 --> 00:42:32,960
Yes, I am.

691
00:42:32,960 --> 00:42:34,260
Did you have breakfast?

692
00:42:34,530 --> 00:42:35,630
Yes.

693
00:42:35,929 --> 00:42:38,429
You found somewhere
with the good reception!

694
00:42:38,599 --> 00:42:41,500
That's the first thing I did
when I got here.

695
00:42:41,699 --> 00:42:43,070
How's the weather there?

696
00:42:43,469 --> 00:42:46,400
It's a bit sad that I have to
enjoy this alone.

697
00:42:47,239 --> 00:42:48,409
I want to be there.

698
00:42:49,110 --> 00:42:50,280
I miss you.

699
00:42:51,280 --> 00:42:52,340
Me too.

700
00:42:52,679 --> 00:42:55,550
Are we going to meet this Saturday?

701
00:42:56,750 --> 00:42:58,420
- Yes.
- That's good.

702
00:43:09,389 --> 00:43:11,099
(Guardian)

703
00:43:17,139 --> 00:43:19,840
Your call is not connected.

704
00:43:19,940 --> 00:43:21,510
Please leave a message.

705
00:43:34,619 --> 00:43:36,050
(Hang Seung Joo)

706
00:43:36,289 --> 00:43:39,360
I can't talk to you right now.
Sorry.

707
00:43:46,159 --> 00:43:48,199
Where's Polaris?

708
00:43:48,199 --> 00:43:50,440
I could find it quickly in Seoul.

709
00:43:51,139 --> 00:43:54,340
You could find it soon there
as there are not so many stars.

710
00:43:55,070 --> 00:43:58,179
You can't see it well here
as there are so many stars.

711
00:43:59,010 --> 00:44:00,780
Do you know how bright it is here...

712
00:44:01,210 --> 00:44:03,250
at a night with a full moon?

713
00:44:04,550 --> 00:44:06,650
It's as bright as day.

714
00:44:07,090 --> 00:44:08,420
That's nonsense.

715
00:44:08,849 --> 00:44:11,460
You're ignoring me as I don't know
much about those things.

716
00:45:55,590 --> 00:45:56,730
It that a phone call?

717
00:45:58,960 --> 00:46:00,329
Where's my cell phone?

718
00:46:07,440 --> 00:46:08,440
(Guardian)

719
00:46:17,320 --> 00:46:19,320
(Han Seung Joo)

720
00:46:21,820 --> 00:46:23,190
Are you really coming?

721
00:46:23,889 --> 00:46:27,659
The express bus to the nearest city
is only at 10am and 3pm.

722
00:46:27,659 --> 00:46:30,860
The last bus to the town is at 7pm,
so I'll take the 10am bus.

723
00:46:31,059 --> 00:46:33,570
It's hard to come here
after you get off the express bus.

724
00:46:33,630 --> 00:46:35,900
Can you come here all right?
Shall I pick you up?

725
00:46:35,929 --> 00:46:38,000
After I get off the express bus,
I take the intercity bus.

726
00:46:38,000 --> 00:46:40,239
Then I get off at Gucheon-dong,
take the bus again,

727
00:46:40,239 --> 00:46:42,610
get off at Jachori,
and I walk to Ttasoonbaegi.

728
00:46:42,610 --> 00:46:44,340
After that I take
the local bus again, right?

729
00:46:45,039 --> 00:46:47,880
Now I can go there
even with my eyes closed.

730
00:46:48,650 --> 00:46:52,119
We might miss each other
if you come too far.

731
00:46:52,179 --> 00:46:55,250
Come to the town entrance
by the time I arrive there.

732
00:46:55,250 --> 00:46:56,289
Do you get it?

733
00:46:56,349 --> 00:46:58,590
Yes, I do.

734
00:47:44,539 --> 00:47:46,440
(Seoul express bus terminal)

735
00:47:49,610 --> 00:47:51,639
(Station manager Choi)

736
00:47:52,539 --> 00:47:54,050
Hello, Mr. Choi.

737
00:47:54,409 --> 00:47:55,750
I got back from a business trip,

738
00:47:55,750 --> 00:47:57,449
and just saw the proposal
for the Chuseok special.

739
00:47:57,619 --> 00:47:59,949
- Director Han, this isn't enough.
- What?

740
00:48:02,519 --> 00:48:03,590
Now?

741
00:48:03,619 --> 00:48:05,960
You should report to headquarter
on Monday.

742
00:48:06,019 --> 00:48:08,460
So, you have to choose a new item
and make a proposal until tomorrow.

743
00:48:08,590 --> 00:48:10,230
Let's talk about the details
in my office.

744
00:48:10,230 --> 00:48:13,769
Excuse me, Mr. Choi, I'm now...

745
00:48:15,269 --> 00:48:18,170
Mr. Choi. Mr. Choi?

746
00:48:20,670 --> 00:48:22,639
This is driving me crazy!

747
00:48:25,840 --> 00:48:27,150
(Guardian)

748
00:48:27,650 --> 00:48:30,420
You'll be connected
to the voice mail...

749
00:48:30,420 --> 00:48:32,719
Gosh.

750
00:48:38,820 --> 00:48:39,860
(Culture production department
proposal, "Her Rest Area")

751
00:48:47,630 --> 00:48:49,699
Your proposal is not exciting.

752
00:48:49,900 --> 00:48:52,070
That won't bring out high ratings.

753
00:48:52,869 --> 00:48:56,210
Mr. Choi, I'm off today.

754
00:48:56,210 --> 00:48:57,880
If you change the item
so suddenly...

755
00:48:57,880 --> 00:49:00,250
People in broadcasting don't have
a day off.

756
00:49:00,449 --> 00:49:03,550
You're working 24 hours
until the program is on air.

757
00:49:03,650 --> 00:49:05,280
You should know better than that.

758
00:49:05,750 --> 00:49:07,949
The director of the headquarters
supports this item too.

759
00:49:07,949 --> 00:49:11,460
Do you have to delay the briefing
on Monday because of a day-off?

760
00:49:12,860 --> 00:49:14,389
I understand.

761
00:50:27,769 --> 00:50:28,769
(Han Seung Joo)

762
00:50:56,389 --> 00:50:57,829
(Grandma)

763
00:51:02,400 --> 00:51:04,570
- Hello?
- Jak Doo.

764
00:51:04,670 --> 00:51:06,840
You have a parcel delivery.

765
00:51:06,869 --> 00:51:08,309
- A parcel delivery?
- Yes.

766
00:51:08,409 --> 00:51:11,510
Han Seung Joo is the name
of that miss from Seoul, right?

767
00:51:11,679 --> 00:51:14,079
Wait a minute.
I'll go there right away.

768
00:51:22,090 --> 00:51:24,690
Gosh. My goodness.

769
00:51:26,659 --> 00:51:29,489
- You will fall down!
- Gosh, I'm so good.

770
00:51:29,559 --> 00:51:31,199
Goodness, you're so good.

771
00:51:31,260 --> 00:51:34,599
Gosh. Goodness gracious!

772
00:51:35,130 --> 00:51:38,170
- I knew it.
- The one who falls down is out!

773
00:51:38,170 --> 00:51:40,070
Jin, it's your turn.

774
00:51:41,340 --> 00:51:42,809
You threw it very well.

775
00:51:43,579 --> 00:51:46,639
- That's it. Good.
- You're doing good, Jin.

776
00:51:46,679 --> 00:51:48,380
Jin, you're doing great.

777
00:51:48,449 --> 00:51:50,179
Gan Nan and Joong Rye,

778
00:51:50,179 --> 00:51:53,349
you should do this instead of me.

779
00:51:53,349 --> 00:51:56,050
Jin only wants to play with you.

780
00:51:56,050 --> 00:51:58,489
Even though he's young,

